Instead of obeying the King's honorable duel, you activate a stimpack within the armor. The effects of the combat drug sends you on a rampage as you beat the King down with your fists until the heavily damaged gauntlets broke. You at last defeated the King. As you climbed out of the armor to grab your keys, his final words to you were:\n\n"Your...pretty..good."\n\nYou saluted the King's corpse for the epic battle you just had. With the keys now in your possession you decide to rig his corpse with some C4. You didn't bother to look at the explosion as you walked away to your computer room.\n\n"GG well played."\n\nYou muttered as you walked through a teleporter that led you to your computer. You booted up Overwatch with a smile on your face and with no regrets for what you just did.\n\n

You immediately recognize him as the King of Guns who rules over Gundom as a dictator.\n\n[[Continue|Fight or Flight]]\n\n[img[smithandwesteros]]
With your new CMC Combat Suit and gauss rifle, you felt as though you could take this annoying ass king out once and for all.\n\n"You really think you can win that old hunk of junk? Please there's a reason why I-"\n\n"Shut the fuck up!" \n\nYou yelled while firing off a quick burst of your gauss rifle. Once again, the king was taken by surprise and several shots were able to connect before he dashed behind another pillar. Luckily the gauss rifle was loaded with armor piercing (AP) rounds and seemed to do some damage to the king.\n\n"Play time's over fool!" the king yelled.\n\nHe jumped out holding his two pistols gangster style and started firing away. You return fire with your gauss rifle. You held your ground and continued to hold down the trigger ripping pieces of the king's armor off while his powerful magnums were doing the same. Eventually, the both of you ran out of ammo. Your power armor was heavily damaged, but not as bad as his since his armor was built for agility over survivability. Although heavily wounded, the king removed the remains of his armor and said,\n\n"Why don't we go at it the old-fashioned way?"\n\nHe raised both his fists and did a slight 'come at me' gesture with his middle finger.\n\n[[Accept the Duel|Duel]]\n[[Just kick his ass with the armor on|End]]

He quickly dashes toward you while firing both shots from his shotgun. Luckily both shots miss and you return fire with the remaining four shots in your magnum; but the bullets just deflect right off of his armor. You quickly backpedal while reloading your magnum and you return fire once more. It was an intense session of circle strafing, side-stepping, and dodge rolling while exchaning gunfire at the same time.\n\nEventually you found a table to hid yourself behind. You were exhausted from the constant physical activities and you were running low on ammo. While resting the King suddenly shouted...\n\n"It's been fun but I think we need to end this party...WITH A BANG!"\n\nAs soon as he said this he started throwing frag grenades everywhere. Then he pulled out two grenade launchers from seemingly thin air and started firing both of them randomly into the air in order to flush me out from hiding.\n\n"It's time TO MAKE IT RAIN! HAHAHAHAHAHA! You get grenade and you get a grenade and everyone gets a grenade!"\n\n[[Continue|Power Armor]]
You raise your gun and look down the sights carefully lining up the perfect shot. As you get ready to shoot you cock the hammer and pull the trigger. Almost immediately, a second shot was heard along with a loud DING. It turns out the King shot the bullet right out of midair with his inhuman marksmanship. Your eyes meet as he stands out from his chair. With a sly grin he said, \n\n"I was hoping we could get to chat a little bit. Whatever, I never was much of a negotiator anyway."\n\nHis initial laziness suddenly changed to pure bloodlust as he instantly raises his pistols and starts shooting. If you were a second slow you would have been dead already, but your killer instincts kicked in just in time for you to dive behind a pillar. Four shots left.\n\n"You wanna play dirty? I can do that to."\nHe quickly sits on his chair and taps a button. The throne wrapped around him. He was now in a suit of power armor.\n\n"How do you like me now?" he said with a smug grin on his face while loading his double-barreled shotgun.\n\n[[Continue|Boss Battle]]\n\n[img[doomguy]]

Suddenly, you notice something hanging from his pocket, the very thing that started your epic quest. The computer room keys are right there in plain sight. He's distracted, all you need is to take him out and then take the keys. \n\nWould it really be that easy though? He looks pretty strong with all those guns on him and he is just leaving himself wide open to attack. He might have a trick up his sleeve though. \n\nYou flip open the chamber of your magnum and perform a quick ammo check. Five shots. More than enough to put a bullet through that guy's head. Keeping your gun ready, you decide whether you want to [[take him out,|Bang]] [[or make a break for the keys.|Dash]]\n\n[img[keys]]
You sprint towards the keys as fast as you can hoping you can catch him off guard and snatch them before he notices. With inhuman reflexes, he grabs your arm and performs an almost instantaneous counter-throw and puts his magnum at your forehead.\n\n"Ah ah ah, you didn't say the magic word."\nBefore pulling the trigger and blowing your brains out.\n\nGAME OVER\n[[Restart from last checkpoint?|Fight or Flight]]
You have decided to go forward and hope that you will find an exit before you die from asphyxiation.\n\nIt feels as if you have been walking for almost five minutes staright. The longest five minutes since you cannot hold your breath any longer. As if a miracle happened, a hole at the top of the room opens up and ventilates the smoke out. Light comes through and a silhouette of a person sitting in a throne chair appears. You stand in awe and confusion unable to figure out what to do. \n\n[[Approach the silhouette?|Approach]]\n\nOR\n\n[[Just stand and wait.|Wait]]
Bryant Sha
Not knowing what to do, you stand at your current location rooted in fear. You attempt to examine what the silhouette is when the you see the figure move around impatiently. All of a sudden youe hear a loud: \n\n"GET OVER HERE!" \n\nFollowed up by a chain with a spear head at the end. It pierces your left arm and then pulls you off your feet towards the figure. After regaining your senses you look up to see an imposing figure leaning over with a very sly grin.\n\n[[Continue|Caught Between a Rock, and a Hard Place]]\n\n[img[spear]]
